      "Text": "expat security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for expat is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "expat is a stream-oriented XML parser library written in C. expat excels with files too large to fit RAM, and where performance and flexibility are crucial.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nlibexpat before 2.8.0 uses insufficient entropy, and thus hash flooding can occur via a crafted XML document.(CVE-2026-41080)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for expat is now available for master/openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4/openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4/openEuler-24.03-LTS/openEuler-24.03-LTS-Next/openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1/openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2/openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3/openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "expat",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
